Unified macOS/Linux License, version 1

1. DEFINITIONS

"macOS User" means any user running this software on Apple macOS operating system.

"Linux User" means any user running this software on a Linux-based operating system, including any distribution or environment derived from the Linux kernel.

"Microslop Shyndous User" means any user running this software on Microslop Windows software set, perfectly designed for creation of Linux installers (and doing it bad), including environments relying on compatibility layers or legacy abstraction stacks.


